headline: Wynn misses quarterly estimates on weak Macau business
summary: Casino operator Wynn Resorts missed second-quarter profit expectations on Thursday, owing to sluggish Macau business. Shares of the company were down 2% in extended trading. The operator of Wynn Palace and Wynn Macau properties, saw a 9.5% fall in adjusted property operating profit from its Macau operations at $253 million, compared to $280 million a year ago.

headline: Wynn Resorts (NASDAQ:WYNN) Misses Q2 Sales Targets
summary: Luxury hotels and casino operator Wynn Resorts (NASDAQ:WYNN) fell short of the market’s revenue expectations in Q2 CY2025, with sales flat year on year at $1.74 billion. Its non-GAAP profit of $1.09 per share was 9% below analysts’ consensus estimates.

headline: Wynn: Q2 Earnings Snapshot
summary: LAS VEGAS (AP) — Wynn Resorts Ltd. (WYNN) on Thursday reported second-quarter net income of $66.2 million. The Las Vegas-based company said it had profit of 64 cents per share. Earnings, adjusted for non-recurring costs, were $1.09 per share.
